WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.799
what God has in store for us this evening.

00:00:02.799 --> 00:00:05.760
And for many of you here on Wednesdays

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:08.000
throughout the calendar year,

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:11.520
we've been really kind of dealing with a theme

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:12.960
or a thought, if you will,

00:00:12.960 --> 00:00:16.399
throughout the calendar year so far on Wednesdays.

00:00:16.399 --> 00:00:20.139
And really we started out with expressing

00:00:20.139 --> 00:00:23.120
our desire to see God work.

00:00:23.120 --> 00:00:25.120
And we started out in Psalm 119,

00:00:25.120 --> 00:00:26.120
where the Psalmist said,

00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:28.979
"'It is time for thee, Lord, to work,

00:00:28.979 --> 00:00:31.219
"'for they have made void thy law.'"

00:00:31.219 --> 00:00:32.659
And that's where we started

00:00:32.659 --> 00:00:34.779
and talked about this desire,

00:00:34.779 --> 00:00:37.139
this longing to see God work,

00:00:37.139 --> 00:00:40.299
to see God do what only God can do.

00:00:40.299 --> 00:00:42.700
And we focused on that for a little while.

00:00:42.700 --> 00:00:45.779
And then we understood as we kind of expressed

00:00:45.779 --> 00:00:47.139
our desire to see God work,

00:00:47.139 --> 00:00:48.779
but then we acknowledged the fact

00:00:48.779 --> 00:00:51.419
that God has the ability to work.

00:00:51.419 --> 00:00:53.180
And I'm thankful for that.

00:00:53.200 --> 00:00:56.240
God is not growing weary.

00:00:56.240 --> 00:00:58.099
He's not losing any power.

00:00:58.099 --> 00:01:00.880
He's as powerful today as he's ever been.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:02.380
And he is eternal.

00:01:02.380 --> 00:01:03.840
He is outside of time.

00:01:03.840 --> 00:01:06.199
He is the Lord God omnipotent.

00:01:06.199 --> 00:01:08.779
And that should cause us to rejoice

00:01:08.779 --> 00:01:11.959
as we consider the fact that our God

00:01:11.959 --> 00:01:13.819
has the ability to work.

00:01:13.819 --> 00:01:16.680
In 2026 and the environment that we're in

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:20.279
and whatever's going on in your life personally,

00:01:20.279 --> 00:01:22.160
in our lives corporately,

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:23.959
in our nation, in our community,

00:01:23.959 --> 00:01:26.139
God is able to work.

00:01:26.139 --> 00:01:27.639
And we established that.

00:01:27.639 --> 00:01:29.940
We looked through a number of portions of scripture

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:31.120
and examined that.

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:34.220
And then we did this as we realized the fact

00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:37.400
and really the last couple of messages on Wednesdays,

00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:42.400
we've realized the fact that doubt and unbelief limit God.

00:01:43.559 --> 00:01:45.080
The Bible says in Psalm 78

00:01:45.080 --> 00:01:47.680
that they limited the Holy One of Israel.

00:01:47.680 --> 00:01:49.879
It was their doubt, it was their unbelief.

00:01:49.879 --> 00:01:51.919
We focused and looked at the fact

00:01:52.680 --> 00:01:54.120
that the gospels tell us that Jesus

00:01:54.120 --> 00:01:56.239
did not many mighty works there.

00:01:56.239 --> 00:01:57.160
Why?

00:01:57.160 --> 00:01:58.559
Because of their unbelief.

00:01:58.559 --> 00:02:00.160
It wasn't that there weren't people

00:02:00.160 --> 00:02:01.919
that needed to be healed.

00:02:01.919 --> 00:02:05.180
It wasn't that God didn't have the power to do it.

00:02:05.180 --> 00:02:07.680
It was that their unbelief limited

00:02:07.680 --> 00:02:10.279
what God was able to accomplish.

00:02:10.279 --> 00:02:11.880
And so as we begin to think about that

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:14.800
and kind of gone through this calendar year on Wednesdays

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:16.600
and looking at all of these things,

00:02:16.600 --> 00:02:20.559
I began to think about the fact of unbelief and doubt.

00:02:20.559 --> 00:02:22.039
And in the passage of scripture

00:02:22.039 --> 00:02:23.960
in which we were studying there in the gospels

00:02:23.960 --> 00:02:27.119
with the man that was demon possessed that was healed,

00:02:27.119 --> 00:02:29.559
the disciples could not heal him.

00:02:29.559 --> 00:02:31.880
They initially brought him to the disciples

00:02:31.880 --> 00:02:33.080
and they were not able.

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:36.360
And the father of the man brings him to Jesus.

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:41.360
And Jesus, that man says, if thou can't do anything,

00:02:41.360 --> 00:02:44.839
that's the plea of the man to Jesus,

00:02:44.839 --> 00:02:49.080
have compassion on us and help us.

00:02:49.080 --> 00:02:51.880
And Jesus said this, if thou can't believe,

00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:54.559
all things are possible.

00:02:54.559 --> 00:02:57.440
That man responded with something that's so important

00:02:57.440 --> 00:02:59.619
for us to acknowledge even in our own lives

00:02:59.619 --> 00:03:04.619
when he said, I believe, help thou mine unbelief.

00:03:04.660 --> 00:03:09.479
And we find that even thereafter as Jesus healed the man

00:03:09.479 --> 00:03:11.300
and all that transpired there

00:03:11.300 --> 00:03:13.899
and the disciples then privately asked,

00:03:13.899 --> 00:03:16.080
why could not we cast him out?

00:03:16.080 --> 00:03:18.559
And we understand that when you compare Mark

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:23.639
and Matthew that Jesus says because of your unbelief,

00:03:23.639 --> 00:03:24.759
because of your unbelief.

00:03:24.759 --> 00:03:27.000
And how many times maybe in our lives

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:31.000
have we've been guilty of doubt,

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:34.039
of not really believing that God is able.

00:03:34.039 --> 00:03:38.119
I mean, I know intellectually, academically,

00:03:38.119 --> 00:03:42.960
I know but this situation and we kinda can reason

00:03:42.960 --> 00:03:45.020
and logic and what have you.

00:03:45.020 --> 00:03:47.240
And we look here in numbers 13 and 14

00:03:47.240 --> 00:03:48.679
and we're gonna spend the next three weeks

00:03:48.679 --> 00:03:50.559
in these two chapters.

00:03:50.559 --> 00:03:53.919
And some of you as soon as you were turning there

00:03:53.919 --> 00:03:55.919
are familiar with the portion of scripture

00:03:55.919 --> 00:03:59.520
it's where the 12 spies are sent to search out the land

00:03:59.520 --> 00:04:01.020
and to bring back a report.

00:04:01.020 --> 00:04:03.740
And of course, we sing with the Sunday school kids

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:06.139
that there were two that were good,

00:04:06.139 --> 00:04:07.440
there were 10 that were bad

00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:10.160
and Joshua and Caleb bring that good report

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:12.559
and the other 10 that evil report.

00:04:12.559 --> 00:04:14.839
And we begin to acknowledge

00:04:14.839 --> 00:04:17.600
as we study through these portions of scripture

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:19.480
that there was an issue with doubt,

00:04:19.480 --> 00:04:21.200
there was an issue with unbelief

00:04:21.200 --> 00:04:23.679
and begin to think about in our lives

00:04:23.679 --> 00:04:26.880
and understanding that we desire to see God work,

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:29.920
that we acknowledge the fact that God can work

00:04:29.920 --> 00:04:34.000
but we realize that oftentimes it's our own doubt

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:36.000
and unbelief that limits God

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:39.480
from doing what God is able to do.

00:04:39.480 --> 00:04:41.839
And so we look here in these portions of scripture

00:04:41.839 --> 00:04:43.279
in numbers 13 and 14,

00:04:43.279 --> 00:04:46.420
to begin to really try to identify doubt,

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:50.500
to be able to identify how does doubt creep into my life?

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:52.619
How does doubt creep into your life?

00:04:52.619 --> 00:04:55.000
What is it that kind of opens the door

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:57.480
to this doubt or to this unbelief?

00:04:57.480 --> 00:04:59.660
Some of you may remember a number of years ago,

00:04:59.660 --> 00:05:01.700
I don't remember the exact calendar, I didn't look it up

00:05:01.700 --> 00:05:04.320
but a number of years ago we had as our theme

00:05:04.320 --> 00:05:08.079
for our church, increase our faith.

00:05:08.079 --> 00:05:10.239
And that theme was from Luke 17

00:05:10.239 --> 00:05:12.920
and it was more of a topical theme,

00:05:12.920 --> 00:05:14.440
I didn't preach through the book of Luke

00:05:14.440 --> 00:05:15.959
and throughout the calendar year,

00:05:15.959 --> 00:05:18.480
I preached a number of different passages of scripture

00:05:18.480 --> 00:05:22.000
that God would use in your life and in my life

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:24.600
to help our faith to grow, to increase.

00:05:24.600 --> 00:05:28.239
And we looked often at the church at Thessalonica

00:05:28.239 --> 00:05:31.579
and how that they were commended in 2 Thessalonians 1

00:05:31.579 --> 00:05:35.239
for this reason that their faith groweth exceedingly.

00:05:35.239 --> 00:05:38.540
And we had this desire, Lord, I want my faith to increase

00:05:38.540 --> 00:05:40.100
and we know that faith cometh by hearing

00:05:40.959 --> 00:05:41.940
and hearing by the word of God

00:05:41.940 --> 00:05:43.779
and throughout that calendar year,

00:05:43.779 --> 00:05:45.700
and if you were here, you might remember this

00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:48.339
but I tried to use an analogy that would help us

00:05:48.339 --> 00:05:52.220
try to really understand this and I said repeatedly

00:05:52.220 --> 00:05:55.179
that faith could be likened to a flower

00:05:56.380 --> 00:06:01.299
and that doubt or unbelief would be likened to a weed.

00:06:01.299 --> 00:06:04.739
And the problem if you love flowers

00:06:04.739 --> 00:06:07.299
is that you have to hate the weeds

00:06:07.299 --> 00:06:10.859
because the weeds will choke out the flowers.

00:06:10.859 --> 00:06:13.299
And we use some of that analogy

00:06:13.299 --> 00:06:15.179
and some of that imagery, if you will,

00:06:15.179 --> 00:06:18.459
and you begin to understand that you wanna take care of

00:06:18.459 --> 00:06:22.059
and we're getting close to the time where flower gardens

00:06:22.059 --> 00:06:24.140
and vegetable gardens will be planted

00:06:24.140 --> 00:06:25.980
and things will begin to grow

00:06:25.980 --> 00:06:30.119
and you wanna be careful that you identify what's a weed.

00:06:31.660 --> 00:06:33.940
You wanna remove those weeds, right?

00:06:33.940 --> 00:06:37.220
As things begin to grow, as you begin to see the green,

00:06:37.940 --> 00:06:39.059
and you've done all the work,

00:06:39.059 --> 00:06:42.619
but you can't prevent from there being no weeds.

00:06:42.619 --> 00:06:47.140
In fact, weeds seem to be able to grow anywhere, right?

00:06:47.140 --> 00:06:49.940
I mean, they grow in the tiniest little cracks

00:06:49.940 --> 00:06:52.100
in the sidewalk, in the asphalt.

00:06:52.100 --> 00:06:53.779
I mean, they just grow anywhere

00:06:53.779 --> 00:06:55.739
and they'll grow in your garden

00:06:55.739 --> 00:06:57.899
and you wanna be able to identify,

00:06:57.899 --> 00:07:00.540
is this a weed or is this a flower?

00:07:00.540 --> 00:07:02.179
Because when they first start coming up,

00:07:02.179 --> 00:07:05.619
it's the easiest time to deal with them, right?

00:07:06.619 --> 00:07:08.100
And so we need to be able to identify

00:07:08.100 --> 00:07:10.579
what is it that we're going to extract?

00:07:10.579 --> 00:07:12.940
I don't wanna pull the plant

00:07:12.940 --> 00:07:15.160
that's going to produce a beautiful flower.

00:07:15.160 --> 00:07:17.739
I don't wanna pull and extract the plant

00:07:17.739 --> 00:07:19.380
that's gonna produce fruit, no.

00:07:19.380 --> 00:07:21.260
I wanna remove the weeds

00:07:21.260 --> 00:07:23.820
that are gonna choke out the flowers.

00:07:23.820 --> 00:07:25.779
And so with that thought in mind,

00:07:25.779 --> 00:07:27.660
as we look at the portion of scripture here

00:07:27.660 --> 00:07:28.859
in Numbers 13 and 14,

00:07:28.859 --> 00:07:32.179
and we'll primarily this evening be in chapter 13,

00:07:32.179 --> 00:07:34.619
I've really just kinda asked myself this question,

00:07:34.619 --> 00:07:37.179
what causes us to doubt?

00:07:37.179 --> 00:07:40.059
What is it in your life and in my life and our lives

00:07:40.059 --> 00:07:43.399
that will cause us to doubt?

00:07:43.399 --> 00:07:45.540
And we're gonna focus on that this evening.

00:07:45.540 --> 00:07:46.779
Next week, we're gonna talk about

00:07:46.779 --> 00:07:49.100
what are some of the consequences of doubt?

00:07:49.100 --> 00:07:51.200
And then finally, on week number three,

00:07:51.200 --> 00:07:53.980
we're gonna talk about how can we conquer doubt?

00:07:53.980 --> 00:07:56.299
And before we can ever conquer it,

00:07:56.299 --> 00:07:58.299
it's important that we are able to identify

00:07:58.299 --> 00:08:00.820
what causes us to doubt.

00:08:00.820 --> 00:08:02.619
And so look at the passage of scripture with me,

00:08:02.619 --> 00:08:04.899
if you will, begin reading in verse number 25,

00:08:04.899 --> 00:08:06.459
and we'll look at some verses here.

00:08:06.459 --> 00:08:07.779
But the Bible says in verse 25,

00:08:07.779 --> 00:08:11.899
and they returned from searching of the land after 40 days.

00:08:11.899 --> 00:08:14.299
And the Bible says in verse 26,

00:08:14.299 --> 00:08:17.019
and they went and came to Moses and to Aaron

00:08:17.019 --> 00:08:19.459
and to all the congregation of the children of Israel

00:08:19.459 --> 00:08:22.380
into the wilderness of Paran to Kadesh,

00:08:22.380 --> 00:08:24.059
and brought back word unto them

00:08:24.059 --> 00:08:26.619
and unto all the congregation.

00:08:26.619 --> 00:08:29.700
Notice it says, and showed them the fruit of the land.

00:08:29.700 --> 00:08:30.940
If you look in verse 23,

00:08:30.980 --> 00:08:33.700
it tells us that they brought back some grapes

00:08:33.700 --> 00:08:35.739
and the one cluster of grapes,

00:08:35.739 --> 00:08:40.739
it was so large that they bear it between two upon a staff.

00:08:40.739 --> 00:08:43.500
So they come back as they had gone out,

00:08:43.500 --> 00:08:46.500
they return after 40 days, they come with this report,

00:08:46.500 --> 00:08:48.500
they show them the fruit of the land.

00:08:48.500 --> 00:08:51.820
And in verse 27, it says, and they told him and said,

00:08:51.820 --> 00:08:55.380
we came unto the land whither thou sentest us.

00:08:55.380 --> 00:08:58.700
And surely it floweth with milk and honey,

00:08:58.700 --> 00:09:00.979
and this is the fruit of it.

00:09:03.059 --> 00:09:05.099
What's the next word in verse 28?

00:09:06.580 --> 00:09:10.780
Nevertheless, things are about to change direction.

00:09:11.820 --> 00:09:12.659
Right?

00:09:12.659 --> 00:09:13.900
If you're familiar with the passage,

00:09:13.900 --> 00:09:15.380
you already know kind of where it's going,

00:09:15.380 --> 00:09:17.140
but I want you to think about this.

00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:20.780
When they come back and they begin to bring this report,

00:09:20.780 --> 00:09:23.500
they come back, they're bearing the fruit.

00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:25.979
They say, they claim in verse 27,

00:09:25.979 --> 00:09:28.700
that we came unto the land whither thou sentest us,

00:09:28.700 --> 00:09:32.260
and surely it floweth with milk and honey.

00:09:32.260 --> 00:09:35.059
And it's a land, this is the fruit of it,

00:09:35.059 --> 00:09:40.059
and they come back, but then they say, nevertheless.

00:09:40.780 --> 00:09:43.099
And what's gonna happen as we look at this portion

00:09:43.099 --> 00:09:45.580
of scripture and really begin to try to identify doubt,

00:09:45.580 --> 00:09:48.299
what causes me to doubt, I would say number one,

00:09:48.299 --> 00:09:52.340
there's a faulty perspective, a faulty perspective.

00:09:52.340 --> 00:09:54.380
What happens as we continue to read here

00:09:54.380 --> 00:09:57.140
and we'll pick back up in verse 28

00:09:57.140 --> 00:09:58.520
and read the next few verses,

00:09:58.520 --> 00:10:00.419
but I want you to notice as we begin.

00:10:00.419 --> 00:10:02.619
to read how that their perspective,

00:10:02.619 --> 00:10:06.779
what they're focused upon becomes the circumstances,

00:10:06.779 --> 00:10:10.179
the obstacles, instead of the Lord.

00:10:10.179 --> 00:10:14.779
They see that this is a land that is a pleasant land.

00:10:14.779 --> 00:10:17.419
This is the fruit, it flows with milk and honey.

00:10:17.419 --> 00:10:19.519
Nevertheless, notice in verse 28,

00:10:19.519 --> 00:10:23.499
it says the people be strong that dwell in the land.

00:10:23.499 --> 00:10:25.779
The cities are walled and very great.

00:10:25.779 --> 00:10:29.499
Moreover, we saw the children of Anak there.

00:10:29.579 --> 00:10:31.379
Those are the giants.

00:10:31.379 --> 00:10:33.459
So begin to bring this report

00:10:33.459 --> 00:10:37.099
and they're bringing this positive perspective in verse 27,

00:10:37.099 --> 00:10:40.359
but then nevertheless, and you can begin to notice

00:10:40.359 --> 00:10:42.819
as we read through the remainder of chapter 13,

00:10:42.819 --> 00:10:47.179
how their focus, their perspective is on the obstacles.

00:10:47.179 --> 00:10:49.339
It's no longer on the Lord.

00:10:49.339 --> 00:10:52.419
The Bible says that they notice these things

00:10:52.419 --> 00:10:55.339
and they mention about the people that are there

00:10:55.339 --> 00:10:57.979
that they're strong, the cities that are there

00:10:57.979 --> 00:11:00.359
that they're walled and that the giants,

00:11:00.359 --> 00:11:02.139
the children of Anak are there.

00:11:02.139 --> 00:11:05.019
In verse 29, the Amalekites dwell in the land of the South

00:11:05.019 --> 00:11:07.499
and the Hittites and the Jebusites and the Amorites

00:11:07.499 --> 00:11:11.519
dwell in the mountains and the Canaanites dwell by the sea

00:11:11.519 --> 00:11:14.019
and by the coast of Jordan.

00:11:14.019 --> 00:11:16.319
The Bible tells us that Caleb steals the people

00:11:16.319 --> 00:11:18.879
in verse 30 before Moses and said,

00:11:18.879 --> 00:11:21.119
"'Let us go up at once and possess it,

00:11:21.119 --> 00:11:22.879
"'for we are well able to overcome it.'"

00:11:22.879 --> 00:11:26.099
By the way, praise the Lord for Caleb and Joshua.

00:11:26.099 --> 00:11:29.679
But the 10, they were able to influence

00:11:29.679 --> 00:11:31.059
the entire congregation.

00:11:32.339 --> 00:11:34.699
The Bible tells us in verse 32,

00:11:34.699 --> 00:11:36.699
and I'll come back to verse 31 in just a moment,

00:11:36.699 --> 00:11:37.539
but in verse 32, it says,

00:11:37.539 --> 00:11:40.039
"'And they brought up an evil report of the land

00:11:40.039 --> 00:11:41.939
"'which they had searched unto the children of Israel,

00:11:41.939 --> 00:11:44.679
"'saying, the land through which we have gone to search

00:11:44.679 --> 00:11:48.319
"'it is a land that eateth up the inhabitants thereof,

00:11:48.319 --> 00:11:50.439
"'and all the people that we saw in it

00:11:50.439 --> 00:11:52.939
"'are men of great stature.

00:11:52.939 --> 00:11:55.259
"'There we saw the giants, the sons of Anak,

00:11:55.299 --> 00:11:56.419
"'which come of the giants,

00:11:56.419 --> 00:11:59.739
"'and we were in our own sight as grasshoppers,

00:11:59.739 --> 00:12:03.219
"'and so we were in their sight.'"

00:12:03.219 --> 00:12:05.099
I want you to think about the perspective

00:12:05.099 --> 00:12:07.339
and really where they're focused

00:12:07.339 --> 00:12:09.219
as we read through this portion of scripture

00:12:09.219 --> 00:12:12.219
and how their focus, their perspective,

00:12:12.219 --> 00:12:15.859
how it changes in their outlook entirely

00:12:15.859 --> 00:12:18.699
and how that doubt begins to creep in.

00:12:18.699 --> 00:12:21.099
See, we all face obstacles.

00:12:21.099 --> 00:12:22.979
We all face difficulties.

00:12:22.979 --> 00:12:25.379
And the reality is, what do we focus on?

00:12:25.379 --> 00:12:28.259
What is our attention on?

00:12:28.259 --> 00:12:30.259
We find that the scriptures would teach us

00:12:30.259 --> 00:12:31.979
in Hebrews chapter number 12,

00:12:31.979 --> 00:12:35.859
looking unto Jesus, the author and finisher of our faith,

